The Cessna hit two adults and a child at an airfield on the approximately 950-metre high Wasserkuppe plateau in the central state of Hesse, according to a report. BERLIN - Three people were killed and several injured when a light aircraft crashed into a group of onlookers in Germany on Sunday, said media reports citing police. The Cessna hit two adults and a child at an airfield on the approximately 950-metre high Wasserkuppe plateau in the central state of Hesse, reported national news agency DPA. The accident happened at around 13.45 GMT, in clear weather conditions, when the machine aborted a landing manoeuvre and sought to gain elevation again. Bild daily reported that another eight people had been injured, quoting local police.